Loyalists of Osun Governor Adegboyega Oyetola and Minister of Interior, Rauf Aregbesola have traded blame after hoodlums clashed in Ikirun on Tuesday. The Nation gathered that the loyalists of Rauf Aregbesola under the caucus of The Osun Progressives (TOP) had converged beside the secretariat of Ifelodun Local Government to hold Ifelodun/Boripe/Odo-Otin Federal Consistency party meeting when the incident occurred. It was learnt officials of the local government approached them to demand the permission letter they obtained to have a meeting beside the road via the Secretariat. A security source said: “There was an altercation at that point and the APC members attacked the officials in the presence of the police and Civil Defence. Later, another set of hoodlums repelled the attack. In the process, people were injured.”   Why I am asking Atiku for divorce, by wife     How Dowen College student Sylvester Omoroni died, by family…     Ex-Lagos Gov Ambode breaks silence on 2023   The Secretary of Aregbesola’s caucus Adelani Baderinwa alleged that Caretaker Chairman of the Council, Mr Hassan Okanlawon, led the attack on them twice. - Advertisement - He alleged: “The hoodlums attacked us again when Rasak Salinsile wanted to give his speech.” Okanlawon however said it was Aregbesola’s supporters that attacked him and others. “Aregbesola’s supporters injured two people at the scene. I was also injured because I questioned why they were holding their meeting beside the road and without permission from the police. They disrupted the activities of the secretariat today. It was a terrible attack,” he stated.